    "content": "In the beginning, the @[Limani Supplies Dealer](organization:5e89421c-6ff3-4051-bdeb-d087f1934349) used @[messengers](profession:945e5e08-bf52-4956-863f-8f2bbad27b68) to send parchment letters and small parcels to their @[merchants](profession:5e33d5a0-cc51-4bf5-8515-131b0c9297a8) and @[wandering merchants](profession:b886db16-9b1b-4940-b1b5-eeec896a91ed) on the road. However, they soon noticed that the messengers were rather slow even when delivering on a @[Tezz](species:6e666bef-b546-43b4-a6e6-e0b3ed76373a), so they decided to develop their own system.\r\n\r\n[quote]I'll give it to you, this is the most delicious surprise you've created and very useful too!|The Limani Trading Master[/quote]\r\n\r\n[h2]Capitalizing on Happy Accidents[/h2]\r\nInspired by the @[Phoenix](species:a842ad50-85ca-4e30-ac45-b39cf8330ecf), the @[Limani Trading Master](rank:6e4e1457-171b-4c08-99e6-da5561a75f42) asked the @[Magi Heptagon](organization:7a195a13-72e0-44c9-a443-4a9f37e07084) to clone the bird. In one of their first real attempts, an accident occured resulting in the birth of the @[WafflePhoenix](species:e1570f33-4ba3-4948-b5df-22d0edfb3348). The Trading Master was very happy to see the bird sitting on his lap thinking it was a clone of an actual phoenix. However, in mere seconds after cloning, it died, turning into a plate of waffles.\r\n\r\nWith the biggest smile on his face, he asked the mages to improve the lifetime of the bird. With a small army of WafflePhoenixes at his disposal, he brought a group of handimen together to build the first two @[Phoenixeries](landmark:d4e250ab-1bef-4552-9b6f-ab8cf23fc7b4); one in @[Limani](settlement:4013fda7-abda-4636-b0a8-fd64854d741d) near @[HQ](landmark:a7696445-8189-4ed4-a4e1-0cd926f57515) and one in @[Matona](settlement:ed81f438-3853-4cff-85f2-5b7e233024b1) near their establishment there. The company tried using the birds for a full year to see how much the speed of arrival increased before rolling it out in full. There was a significant increase in speed but also in information leaking.\r\n\r\nTo tackle this problem, the Limani Trading Master capitalised on the biggest asset of the messaging system: the WafflePhoenix. With these phoenixes turning into a plate of waffles upon their death, he figured there must be something they can do to replicate the same process but with parchment. Once again, he went to the @[Magi Heptagon](organization:7a195a13-72e0-44c9-a443-4a9f37e07084) to discuss and experiment. Out of this came the @[Limani Supplies Dealer Messages](item:0d16f47e-00c0-49fe-beb0-6c468442cb8b), a special parchment that turns into syrup to accomodate the waffles when its carries dies. Turning delicious twists into extra safety precautions has become a staple at the merchant guild. Unfortunately, it only works for messages as the paper itself turns into syrup which is why parcels are rarely sent by bird.\r\n\r\nNowadays, everyone in @[Eshil](location:251eb80c-8462-4cd2-ae93-dbb4ecb74af8) uses this system to send messages to one another. Some homes own a @[WafflePhoenix](species:e1570f33-4ba3-4948-b5df-22d0edfb3348) themselves, others go to a @[Phoenixery](landmark:d4e250ab-1bef-4552-9b6f-ab8cf23fc7b4) to rent one for sending their messages. It doesn't generate much for the @[Limani Supplies Dealer](organization:5e89421c-6ff3-4051-bdeb-d087f1934349); they want to provide this as a service to their community.",
